body:
@zentol I aggregated results by SonarQube.
I can share some overall report.
[flink.pdf](https://github.com/apache/flink/files/612971/flink.pdf)

I moved default value from `SimpleStateDescriptor` to `ValueStateDescriptor`. Now only `ValueStateDescriptor`s have default values.  The serialization methods may contain some duplicated code, but i think it's acceptable.

I also modify the implementation of `HeapReducingState`s. The first value will be copied before being put into the heap.

@aljoscha What do you think of these changes?

@thvasilo I think that should be handled in a separate PR. 

@StephanEwen Yes, I think this is a good differentiation to make in the docs. If it is not possible to write Flink programs with Eclipse, then we have a problem. I really hope that it is possible and we should check this. @NicoK Did you try to write a Flink program with Eclipse, for example using quick starts?

I think it's fine to drop the docs for Flink core dev with Eclipse if it is not possible to get it done in a straight forward manner. @vasia Do you have any input on this?
